Nodes.Text: Simple calculator API hosted on APIMATIC for demo purposes

The generated code uses the Newtonsoft Json.NET NuGet Package. If the automatic NuGet package restore is enabled, these dependencies will be installed automatically. Therefore, you will need internet access for build.
* Open the solution (APIMATICCalculatorTest.sln) file.
Invoke the build process using Ctrl + Shift + B shortcut key or using the Build menu as shown below.
The build process generates a portable class library, which can be used like a normal class library. More information on how to use can be found at the MSDN Portable Class Libraries documentation.

The supported version is **.NET Standard 2.0**. For checking compatibility of your .NET implementation with the generated library, [click here](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/en-us/platform/dotnet-standard#versions).
The following section explains how to use the APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard library in a new project.
For starting a new project, right click on the current solution from the solution explorer and choose `Add -> New Project`.

Nodes.AlterateText: Add a new project in Visual Studio

Nodes.Text: Next, choose `Console Application`, provide `TestConsoleProject` as the project name and click OK.

Nodes.AlterateText: Create a new Console Application in Visual Studio

Nodes.Text: The new console project is the entry point for the eventual execution. This requires us to set the `TestConsoleProject` as the start-up project. To do this, right-click on the `TestConsoleProject` and choose `Set as StartUp Project` form the context menu.

In order to use the `APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard` library in the new project, first we must add a project reference to the `TestConsoleProject`. First, right click on the `References` node in the solution explorer and click `Add Reference...`

Next, a window will be displayed where we must set the `checkbox` on `APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard` and click `OK`. By doing this, we have added a reference of the `APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard` project into the new `TestConsoleProject`.

Steps.Title: Add reference of the library project

Nodes.Text: Once the `TestConsoleProject` is created, a file named `Program.cs` will be visible in the solution explorer with an empty `Main` method. This is the entry point for the execution of the entire solution. Here, you can add code to initialize the client library and acquire the instance of a Controller class. Sample code to initialize the client library and using Controller methods is given in the subsequent sections.
The following parameters are configurable for the API Client:
The API client can be initialized as follows:

APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard.APIMATICCalculatorTestClient client = new APIMATICCalculatorTest.Standard.APIMATICCalculatorTestClient.Builder()
    .Build();
Parameters for retries can be configured through the HttpClientConfiguration in the API Client:

Data:
Number of times the request is retried.
*Default*: `0`

Exponential backoff factor for duration between retry calls.
*Default*: `2`

The time interval between the endpoint calls.
*Default*: `1`

List of Http request methods to invoke retry.
*Default*: `"GET", "PUT", "GET", "PUT"`
